## 8. API Route Specification\
\
**Endpoint:** `POST /api/art-official/chat`\
\
**Request body:**\
```typescript\
\{\
  messages: AnthropicMessage[],      // full conversation history\
  imageUrl?: string,                  // present after upload\
  sessionId: string,                  // links to session record in Payload\
  artistId: string                    // for access control\
\}\
```\
\
**Response body:**\
```typescript\
\{\
  message: string,                    // agent's conversational response\
  fieldUpdates: FieldUpdate[],        // array of update_field calls from this turn\
  sessionFieldUpdates: SessionField[] // array of store_session_field calls\
\}\
```\
\
**Server-side flow:**\
1. Authenticate request against Payload session\
2. Pull Practice Knowledge from Payload, assemble system prompt\
3. Call Anthropic API with assembled system prompt, full message history, image (if present), tool definitions\
4. Parse response \'97 extract conversational text and tool calls\
5. Apply field updates to the session record in Payload\
6. Return message and field updates to client\
\
**Model:** `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`\
\
**Max tokens:** 1024 per turn (conversational responses should be short)\
\
**Tools:** Pass all four tools defined in Section 4 of this document.\
\
