## 9. Career-Stage Field Visibility\
\
### 9.1 Why this exists\
\
An artist earlier in their career will not have works in auction databases, institutional collections, or authenticated provenance chains. Presenting fields for auction estimates, institutional loan history, or authentication records to an artist at that stage is disorienting \'97 it implies expectations that don't apply, and clutters the session with questions that have no answers yet.\
\
The solution is not to remove these fields from the schema. They belong there \'97 the architecture is designed to grow with the practice. The solution is to make them invisible to the dialogue until they are relevant, and to provide a clear path to populate them when they become relevant.\
\
### 10.2 The three tiers\
\
**Tier 1 \'97 Studio**\
\
The default state for all artists. Covers everything needed to build a complete, rich catalogue record at the point of making: all identity, physical, intent, art historical, classification, commercial, and basic provenance fields. This is the full cataloguing session as specified in Sections 3\'967 of this document.\
\
Fields active at Tier 1:\
- All identity fields (`title`, `yearCreated`, `series`, `city`, etc.)\
- All physical fields (dimensions, medium, support, framing, condition)\
- All intent and reflection fields (`intent`, `makingNote`, `directInspiration`, `encounterNote`, etc.)\
- All classification fields (tags, `conceptualKeywords`, `artHistoricalReferences`)\
- All commercial fields limited to studio context (`availabilityStatus`, `listingCurrency`, `askingPrice`, `editions`)\
- Provenance as artist-confirmed studio origin: `currentLocation` defaults to `artist's studio`; `ownershipHistory` starts with the studio entry\
\
Fields dormant at Tier 1 (silently skipped in dialogue):\
- `salesRecord` auction channel entries\
- `auctionHouse`, `auctionEstimateHistory`, `resaleDelta`\
- `consignmentDetails`, `galleryReference`\
- `loanHistory` with institutional context\
- `authenticationRecord`, `institutionalDependencyRecord`, `validationFlowRecord`\
- `provenanceConfidenceLayer` beyond the default studio entry\
\
**Tier 2 \'97 Market**\
\
Activated when the artist's work has entered the secondary market or is represented by a gallery with an ongoing sales programme. Commercial and provenance fields expand to include auction and gallery infrastructure.\
\
Additional fields active at Tier 2:\
- `salesRecord` full object including `auctionHouse` and `channel: 'auction'` entries\
- `auctionEstimateHistory` (pre-sale estimate vs hammer price per auction appearance)\
- `resaleDelta` (gap between artist's original sale price and resale price \'97 the financial extraction record)\
- `consignmentDetails` (gallery name and date when `availabilityStatus: 'on consignment'`)\
- `galleryReference` (gallery's own inventory number)\
\
**Tier 3 \'97 Institutional**\
\
Activated when the artist's work has entered institutional collections, been the subject of authenticated exhibition at significant institutions, or when loan history is materially relevant to the record.\
\
Additional fields active at Tier 3:\
- `loanHistory` with full institutional context (institution name, dates, linked event)\
- `authenticationRecord` (who authenticated, evidence basis, financial relationship to outcome)\
- `institutionalDependencyRecord` (structural commitments made by institutions to donors \'97 relevant when the work enters a collection shaped by donor influence)\
- `validationFlowRecord` (which institutional validations are independent vs structurally entangled)\
- `provenanceConfidenceLayer` (full form \'97 evidence basis and confidence level per ownership claim)\
\
### 10.3 How the agent reads career stage\
\
The `careerStage` field lives on the Artist record (see `master-schema-spec.md` Section 3.4). Values: `studio` | `market` | `institutional`. Set manually by the artist or admin. Defaults to `studio`.\
\
At session start, the API route reads `careerStage` from the Artist singleton and passes it into the system prompt as part of Section 1 (Identity and Role). The agent uses it to filter the field roadmap silently. No mention of tiers or skipped fields is ever made in the conversation.\
\
### 10.4 Populating dormant fields later\
\
Dormant fields are not lost \'97 they are waiting. Two paths to populate them when they become relevant:\
\
**Manual entry.** The artist accesses the standard Payload Artworks admin at any time and fills dormant fields directly. The Payload admin shows all fields regardless of career stage \'97 the tier logic is a dialogue-layer filter only, not a schema restriction.\
\
**Background enrichment agent.** A separate, non-session process that queries public sources \'97 Artnet, auction house databases, exhibition catalogues, institutional collection records \'97 and pre-populates dormant fields as `confidence: 'inferred'`, `source: 'enrichment-agent'` values. These appear in the admin as agent-suggested and pending artist confirmation. The enrichment agent is not part of the cataloguing session architecture and is not specified here \'97 it is a future build that the schema and field confidence system are already designed to accommodate.\
\
### 10.5 Cursor implementation note\
\
Add `careerStage` (select: `studio` | `market` | `institutional`, default: `studio`) to the Artist collection in `src/collections/Artist.ts`. The `/api/art-official/chat` route reads this value at session start and includes it in the system prompt assembly. No UI changes to the Artworks collection are required \'97 the tier logic lives entirely in the dialogue layer, not the schema.\
\
