## 10. Sessions Collection Specification\
\
Every Art/Official session \'97 whether an artwork cataloguing session or a statement dialogue session \'97 writes to a `Sessions` collection in Payload. This collection is the working record behind every confirmed artwork. It serves two purposes: it stores the full session data needed to reconstruct what happened, and it is the primary tool for refining the dialogue spec over time through annotated testing.\
\
### 10.1 Why a Sessions collection\
\
The confirmed Artworks record is the clean output. The Sessions record is the full working document \'97 the transcript, the timing of field confirmations, the blind description, the agent's drafts before the artist edited them. Without it, there is no way to go back and understand why a session produced weak `intent` material, or where the weave broke down, or what the agent's first `formalContributionAssessment` draft looked like before it was rewritten.\
\
For the testing phase specifically, the Sessions collection is how the dialogue spec gets refined. After each test session, the transcript is read back, annotated, and the spec is updated. Over three or four sessions the dialogue will sharpen considerably.\
\
### 10.2 Collection fields\
\
**Identity**\
\
| Field | Type | Notes |\
|---|---|---|\
| `sessionId` | text | Auto-generated UUID. Never changes. |\
| `sessionType` | select | `artwork-cataloguing` \\| `artist-statement` \\| `biography` \\| `onboarding` |\
| `status` | select | `in-progress` \\| `completed` \\| `abandoned` |\
| `artworkRecord` | relation \uc0\u8594  Artworks | Populated at confirmation commit. Null if session abandoned or statement type. |\
| `createdAt` | date | Session start timestamp. Auto-generated. |\
| `completedAt` | date | Session end timestamp. Set at confirmation commit. |\
| `artistId` | relation \uc0\u8594  Artist | Which artist this session belongs to. |\
\
**Transcript**\
\
| Field | Type | Notes |\
|---|---|---|\
| `messages` | JSON | Full conversation history in Anthropic message format. Every turn, in order. Never truncated. |\
| `firstImpression` | longText | The blind description from the pre-upload phase. Private. |\
| `secondDescription` | longText | The description given in Phase 6 after the conversation. Private. |\
| `fieldUpdateTimeline` | JSON | Array of `\{ field, value, confidence, source, timestamp \}` \'97 every `update_field` call in sequence. Shows which fields confirmed early, which came late, which were never confirmed. |\
\
**Agent drafts \'97 pre-edit versions**\
\
These fields store what the agent generated before the artist edited at confirmation. Comparing these to the final confirmed values is where the most useful refinement signal lives.\
\
| Field | Type | Notes |\
|---|---|---|\
| `agentDraftDescriptionShort` | text | Agent's generated draft before artist edit. |\
| `agentDraftDescriptionLong` | richText | Agent's generated draft before artist edit. |\
| `agentDraftConceptualKeywords` | text[] | Agent's generated keywords before artist edit. |\
| `agentDraftFormalContribution` | longText | Agent's generated formalContributionAssessment draft before artist edit. |\
\
**Testing and refinement annotations**\
\
These fields are filled by the artist after the session, not during it. They are the annotation layer for dialogue refinement.\
\
| Field | Type | Notes |\
|---|---|---|\
| `sessionNotes` | richText | Free-form artist annotation after the session. What worked, what didn't, what felt wrong in the dialogue. |\
| `weakPhases` | select[] | Which phases produced thin or defended material. Values: `orientation` \\| `physical` \\| `classification` \\| `intent` \\| `making` \\| `inspiration` \\| `artHistorical` \\| `consciousRejections` \\| `encounterNote` \\| `confirmation` |\
| `blindDescriptionUseful` | boolean | Did the blind description produce material the later conversation didn't? |\
| `formalContributionAccuracy` | select | How close was the agent's draft to what the artist actually thinks? Values: `close` \\| `partial` \\| `off` \\| `completely-wrong` |\
| `dialogueRefinementFlag` | boolean | Flag this session for dialogue spec review. |\
| `refinementNotes` | longText | Specific notes for spec refinement \'97 what question should have been asked differently, where the weave broke, what the block-handling missed. |\
\
### 10.3 Access control\
\
Sessions are private to the artist and admin role for direct collection access (read/create/update/delete via Payload admin or local API). A separate, public Tier 5 API path exists for machine-readable corpus access (see `sessions-tier5-machine-access-spec.md`), keyed by artwork slug, for `completed` sessions only. This path exposes both the artist's reasoning trail (`artistRecord`) and the dialogue system's own process-integrity notes (`artism:DialogueSelfAudit`), kept in clearly separated, distinctly-namespaced nodes so the two are never confused with one another. The `messages` and `firstImpression` fields remain sensitive in the collection itself \'97 they are only released through that labeled Tier 5 path, never via anonymous collection REST.\
\
```typescript\
access: \{\
  read: artistOrAdmin,\
  create: artistOrAdmin,\
  update: artistOrAdmin,\
  delete: artistOrAdmin,\
\}\
```\
\
### 10.4 Session record lifecycle\
\
1. **Session start** \'97 record created with `status: in-progress`, `sessionId` generated, `createdAt` set.\
2. **During session** \'97 `messages` array updated on every turn. `fieldUpdateTimeline` updated on every `update_field` tool call. `firstImpression` stored when blind description is received.\
3. **Phase 6** \'97 `secondDescription` stored when second description is given.\
4. **Confirmation commit** \'97 `artworkRecord` relation populated, `status` set to `completed`, `completedAt` set. Agent drafts stored in the draft fields before the artist's confirmed versions are written to the Artworks record.\
5. **Post-session annotation** \'97 artist fills `sessionNotes`, `weakPhases`, `blindDescriptionUseful`, `formalContributionAccuracy`, `dialogueRefinementFlag`, `refinementNotes` at any point after the session.\
\
### 10.5 Cursor implementation instructions\
\
Create `src/collections/Sessions.ts`. This collection has no dependencies on other collections except Artist and Artworks \'97 implement it after both exist.\
\
The `messages` field is a JSON field storing the raw Anthropic message array. Do not attempt to parse or validate its internal structure at the Payload level \'97 store it as opaque JSON.\
\
The `fieldUpdateTimeline` field is a JSON array. Each entry has the shape:\
```typescript\
\{\
  field: string,\
  value: any,\
  confidence: 'confirmed' | 'inferred',\
  source: 'conversation' | 'image-analysis' | 'knowledge-base',\
  timestamp: string // ISO date string\
\}\
```\
\
The `weakPhases` field is a multi-select \'97 the artist can flag more than one weak phase per session.\
\
The admin view for Sessions should show: session type, status, linked artwork (if any), created date, and the `dialogueRefinementFlag` as a prominent visual indicator. Sessions flagged for refinement should be visually distinct in the list view \'97 this is how the queue for spec review stays visible.\
\
Do not build a public-facing view for Sessions. This collection is admin-only.\
\
\uc0\u10003  Create a test session record manually in the admin. Verify all fields accept correct types. Verify the `artworkRecord` relation links correctly to an existing Artwork. Verify the collection does not appear in any public API response.\
\
